# ğŸ› ï¸ Setup Instructions: OwnCloud Docker Deployment

This guide walks you through the steps to deploy a self-hosted OwnCloud server using Docker Compose with HTTPS, monitoring, and secure networking.

---

## âœ… Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following:

- A Linux server or VM (Debian/Ubuntu recommended)
- Docker and Docker Compose installed
- A domain name (e.g., from DuckDNS)
- Ports 80 and 443 open and forwarded (if behind NAT/router)
- Your `.env` file created based on `.env.example`
- Sudo privileges

---

## ğŸ“¦ Install Required Packages

### Docker & Docker Compose

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y \
  apt-transport-https \
  ca-certificates \
  curl \
  software-properties-common

# Docker
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh
sudo sh get-docker.sh

# Docker Compose
sudo curl -L "https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/2.24.6/docker-compose-$(uname -s)-$(uname -m)" -o /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/docker-compose

# Verify installation
docker --version
docker-compose --version

# Set Up DuckDNS (Dynamic DNS)
Sign up at https://www.duckdns.org

Create a subdomain (e.g., tylerscloudsvm.duckdns.org)

Update your router/firewall to port forward:

80 â†’ 80 (HTTP)

443 â†’ 443 (HTTPS)


# Project Structure
Ensure your folders are structured like this:


owncloud-docker-setup/
