## Configure .env File
Create your own .env file from the provided example:


cp .env.example .env
nano .env
Edit the values for:

OWNCLOUD_DOMAIN

TRAEFIK_EMAIL

ADMIN_USERNAME and ADMIN_PASSWORD

OWNCLOUD_DB_USERNAME and OWNCLOUD_DB_PASSWORD

DUCKDNS_TOKEN if applicable

## Start the Stack
From your project root:


docker-compose up -d
Verify all containers are running:


docker-compose ps
